\subtree{
\title{Common Pitfalls to Avoid}
\subtree{
\title{Case Reports}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Privacy violations}: Inadequate de-identification or missing consent}
\li{\strong{Lack of novelty}: Reporting common or well-documented cases}
\li{\strong{Insufficient detail}: Missing key clinical information}
\li{\strong{Poor literature review}: Failure to contextualize within existing knowledge}
\li{\strong{Overgeneralization}: Drawing broad conclusions from single case}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Diagnostic Reports}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Vague language}: Using ambiguous terms like "unremarkable" without specifics}
\li{\strong{Incomplete comparison}: Not reviewing prior imaging}
\li{\strong{Missing clinical correlation}: Failing to answer clinical question}
\li{\strong{Technical jargon}: Overuse of terminology without explanation}
\li{\strong{Delayed critical value notification}: Not communicating urgent findings}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Clinical Trial Reports}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Late reporting}: Missing regulatory deadlines for SAE reporting}
\li{\strong{Incomplete causality}: Inadequate causality assessment}
\li{\strong{Data inconsistencies}: Discrepancies between data sources}
\li{\strong{Protocol deviations}: Unreported or inadequately documented deviations}
\li{\strong{Selective reporting}: Omitting negative or unfavorable results}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Patient Documentation}
\ul{
\li{\strong{Illegibility}: Poor handwriting in paper records}
\li{\strong{Copy-forward errors}: Propagating outdated information}
\li{\strong{Insufficient detail}: Vague or incomplete documentation affecting billing}
\li{\strong{Lack of medical necessity}: Not documenting indication for services}
\li{\strong{Missing signatures}: Unsigned or undated notes}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Final Checklist}
\p{Before finalizing any clinical report, verify:}

\ul{
\li{[ ] All required sections complete}
\li{[ ] Patient privacy protected (HIPAA compliance)}
\li{[ ] Informed consent obtained (if applicable)}
\li{[ ] Accurate and verified clinical data}
\li{[ ] Appropriate medical terminology and coding}
\li{[ ] Clear, professional language}
\li{[ ] Proper formatting per guidelines}
\li{[ ] References cited appropriately}
\li{[ ] Figures and tables labeled correctly}
\li{[ ] Spell-checked and proofread}
\li{[ ] Regulatory requirements met}
\li{[ ] Institutional policies followed}
\li{[ ] Signatures and dates present}
\li{[ ] Quality assurance review completed}
}

\p{\strong{Final Note}: Clinical report writing requires attention to detail, medical accuracy, regulatory compliance, and clear communication. Whether documenting patient care, reporting research findings, or communicating diagnostic results, the quality of clinical reports directly impacts patient safety, healthcare delivery, and medical knowledge advancement. Always prioritize accuracy, privacy, and professionalism in all clinical documentation.}
}
}